Package: nanolx-games-emu
Architecture: all
Depends: dolphin-emu | bash,
         dosbox,
         lxdream,
         mupen64plus,
         mupen64plus-audio-all,
         mupen64plus-video-arachnoid,
         mupen64plus-video-glide64,
         mupen64plus-video-rice,
         mupen64plus-video-z64,
         nestopia,
         snes9x-gtk,
         yabause-gtk,
         gnuboy-sdl,
         scummvm,
         visualboyadvance-gtk,
         desmume,
         fceux
Description: Collection of emulators
 This meta-package installs a collection of emulators.
 .
 NOTE: only use self-made ROMs (using homebrew, hardware mods, or
       tools like Retrode). Downloading ROMs is often illegal. Known
       exceptions: ROMs where the copyright expired, ROMs distributed
       by the copyright holder (or it's legal successor) and Homebrew
       ROMs (completely self-made).
 .
 These are:
 - gnuboy-sdl (Game Boy, Game Boy Color)
 - visualboyadvance-gtk (Game Boy Advance)
 - desmume (Nintendo DS)
 - nestopia (Famicom / NES)
 - snex9x-gtk (Super Famicom / SNES)
 - mupen64plus (Nintendo 64)
 - dolphin-emu (GameCube / Wii [only amd64])
 - yabause-gtk (SEGA Saturn)
 - lxdream (SEGA DreamCast)
 - dosbox (DOS)
 - scummvm (Lucas Arts Point'n'Click Adventures)

Package: nanolx-games-hacking
Architecture: all
Depends: applyppf3,
         makeppf3,
         cmdpack-uips,
         wit,
         szs,
         patchimage,
         segher-wii-tools,
         devkitppc | bash,
         qwad,
         libfat | bash,
         libruntimeiospatch | bash,
         libogc | bash,
         libogc-7zip | bash,
         libogc-dopmii | bash,
         libogc-expat | bash,
         libogc-ext2fs | bash,
         libogc-freetype | bash,
         libogc-gd | bash,
         libogc-grrlib | bash,
         libogc-jpeg | bash,
         libogc-mupdf | bash,
         libogc-mxml | bash,
         libogc-nfs | bash,
         libogc-ntfs | bash,
         libogc-png | bash,
         libogc-pngu | bash,
         libogc-sdl | bash,
         libogc-smpeg | bash,
         libogc-tiff | bash,
         libogc-tremor | bash,
         libogc-unrar | bash,
         libogc-zip | bash,
         libogc-zlib | bash,
         nand-bin-check,
         nand-dump,
         nand-extract,
         savetoy,
         ohne-schwarzenegger,
         xdelta3
Description: Collection of game hacking tools
 This meta-package installs game hacking tools
 .
 NOTE: only use self-made ROMs (using homebrew, hardware mods, or
       tools like Retrode). Downloading ROMs is often illegal. Known
       exceptions: ROMs where the copyright expired, ROMs distributed
       by the copyright holder (or it's legal successor) and Homebrew
       ROMs (completely self-made).
 .
 These are:
 - applyppf3 / makeppf3 (PlayStation Patch Format)
 - cmdpack-uips (IPS Format)
 - devkitppc / libogc*, libfat, libruntimeiospatch (GameCube / (v)Wii
   homebrew development kit [only i386 and amd64])
 - wit (manipulate GameCube / Wii ISOs)
 - szs (manipulate Mario Kart Wii game data)
 - qwad (download IOS' and channels from NUS (Nintendo Update Server)
   as Wads or manipulate existing Wads)
 - patchimage (download and apply game hacks to a ROM (mostly for
   New Super Mario Bros. Wii and Mario Kart Wii))
 - segher-wii-tools, nand-bin-check, nand-dump, nand-extract, savetoy,
   ohne-schwarzenegger (misc. Wii homebrew utilities)
 - xdelta3
